.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-REDO 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-redo \- redo the most recently undone operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch redo
[\fB\-\-force\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B redo
restores the state that existed before the most recent undo. A new undoable
operation after undo clears the redo stack. By default redo refuses if later
changes make the checkpoint unsafe to apply.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-force
Overwrite changes made after the undo.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-undo (1)
